AGI - Macron > There is no way that the peace negotiations for Ukraine are managed by Donald Trump > and thus passes to the counterattack, convening a EU summit in Paris. >
&nbsp;
The European summit on Ukraine convened in Paris could take place in the Weimar+ format - which includes France, Germany, Poland, Italy, Spain and the United Kingdom - expanded to other European countries. It is reported by the media of the Nordic countries.
<br The date of Monday 17 February has not yet been officially confirmed for the summit, still in progress, but appears more and more likely. Dutch Prime Minister Dick Schoof, also invited to the summit, said in these hours that he will go tomorrow to the French capital. Denmark is also present, which will represent the NB8 block, i.e. the Nordic and Baltic countries.
&nbsp;
The British Prime Minister, Keir Starmer, and NATO Secretary-General, Mark Rutte>, will also participate in the summit of European heads of state and government on the convened Ukraine. The presence of the former Dutch prime minister was confirmed by himself, who urged Europeans to demonstrate their "utility" to play a role in the negotiation of the future of Kiev > between the US and Russia, a table from which Europe was explicitly excluded, as pointed out by the US envoy for Ukraine, Keith Kellogg.
&nbsp;
Europe must "play a more important role within NATO" and collaborate with the United States to "ensure the future of Ukraine", Starmer said, whose presence at the Paris summit is confirmed to the British press by sources of Downing Street. >
&nbsp;
It is not yet confirmed that the summit will be held tomorrow. To give the news yesterday was the Polish Foreign Minister, Radoslaw Sikorski, who at first indicated Sunday as possible data>. From the Elysée they have subsequently clarified that there is nothing definite yet and at the moment there are still consultations. On the other hand, an informal meeting of foreign ministers, convened by Kaja Kallas, High Representative for Foreign Affairs of the European Commission, is scheduled to take place at the Munich Conference. It is probable that a unitary response to the questionnaire sent yesterday by the U.S. administration to European capitals will be discussed here to ask them how they intend to contribute in concrete terms to the security guarantees requested by Ukraine.&nbsp;>

